1. The Semi-Pelagians confeſt that Men are born corrupted, and cannot free themſelves from that Corruption

but by the help of Grace, which is notwithſtanding prevented by ſome Motion of the Will, as by a good Deſire; whence it is that they ſaid, Meum est velle credere, Dei autem gratiae est adjuvare;
                  To be willing to believe depends on me, but 'tis the part of God's Grace to help me. — God, in their Opinion, expects thoſe Firſt Motions from us, and then gives us his Grace.

